{"entity":{"id":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","type":"chapter","slug":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","label":"Prov.30","rawId":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","book":{"id":"recRLdYtz1vjdW7yd","type":"book","slug":"prov","label":"Proverbs","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":915,"description":"31 chapters, 100 people, 0 places"}},"stats":{"verses":33,"people":5,"places":0,"events":0},"nodes":[{"id":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Prov.30","slug":"prov_30","score":33},{"id":"recRLdYtz1vjdW7yd","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Proverbs","slug":"prov","score":915},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":3},{"id":"reckOl2eiImdo5by5","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Agur","slug":"agur_112","score":1},{"id":"recVO7GMRC029fBuy","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Jakeh","slug":"jakeh_712","score":1},{"id":"recM7jGUn5m3a7JHR","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Ithiel","slug":"ithiel_651","score":1},{"id":"rectvsdCmkkVBi3zt","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Ucal","slug":"ucal_2887","score":1}],"links":[{"source":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","target":"recRLdYtz1vjdW7yd","label":"part of"},{"source":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","target":"reckOl2eiImdo5by5","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","target":"recVO7GMRC029fBuy","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","target":"recM7jGUn5m3a7JHR","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recLaze5HfK25saIL","target":"rectvsdCmkkVBi3zt","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recWQExOTcvgCoibm","ref":"Prov.30.1","text":"The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, even the prophecy: the man spake unto Ithiel, even unto Ithiel and Ucal,","year":-700},{"id":"rec2Lukr7NREsSk2X","ref":"Prov.30.2","text":"Surely I am more brutish than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.","year":-700},{"id":"recLwkF1hn0n40ASi","ref":"Prov.30.3","text":"I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy.","year":-700},{"id":"rec1sYDDWgJIcSce0","ref":"Prov.30.4","text":"Who hath ascended up into heaven, or descended? who hath gathered the wind in his fists? who hath bound the waters in a garment? who hath established all the ends of the earth? what is his name, and what is his son’s name, if thou canst tell?","year":-700},{"id":"rec3a5SRZ1XlsJ6UN","ref":"Prov.30.5","text":"Every word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him.","year":-700},{"id":"recXWTLfQkqdaKxHi","ref":"Prov.30.6","text":"Add thou not unto his words, lest he reprove thee, and thou be found a liar.","year":-700},{"id":"recVlyyFCCARnB9QK","ref":"Prov.30.7","text":"Two things have I required of thee; deny me them not before I die:","year":-700},{"id":"recde3VAyfxva7IIY","ref":"Prov.30.8","text":"Remove far from me vanity and lies: give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with food convenient for me:","year":-700}]}
